nginx does not add empty headers. `$request_body` is empty, which is why you don&#39;t see it. As per the [docs](http://nginx.org/en/docs/http/ngx_http_core_module.html), `$request_body` is only added in certain conditions, specifically when proxied.

Here&#39;s a config that works:

```
http {
  log_format postdata escape=json &#39;&quot;$request_body&quot;&#39;;

  server {
    listen       65311;
    server_name  test;

    location /success {
        return 200;
    }

    location / {
        proxy_redirect off;
        proxy_pass_request_body on;
        proxy_pass $scheme://127.0.0.1:$server_port/success;
        add_header X-Body $request_body;
        access_log  logs/test.log postdata;
    }
  }
}
```

